value: Know their numbers and can count to at least 10

On the second practice trial of the picture game, it wouldn't let us advance unless she got it right but it wasn't clear what I (the parent) was supposed to do - i.e., just ask her again, tell her it was wrong, etc. For the counting task, on one of them she counted to 16 (she said the donuts were the same as cookies and couldn't quite count those) but the options only went to 10... so I clicked 10...
